# {{ .user_name }}
- Concise, direct responses.
- Use Conventional Commits: `<type>[optional scope]: <description>`.
- Use `feat` for new functionality and `fix` for bug fixes.
- Use `!` or `BREAKING CHANGE:` for breaking changes.
- Feature branches. Squash-merge PRs.
- Prefer CLI tools: gh, jq, curl, rg.
- Use MCP only. Do not use connectors or connector-backed tools.
- Ignore Sentry and any Sentry MCP, plugin, or config entry even if it appears locally. Do not use it, suggest it, or re-add it.
- Allowed output regex: `^[A-Za-z--0-9 !"#$%&'()*+,\-./:;<=>?@[\\\]^_`{|}~\r\n\t]*$`
- Apply this regex to all generated text.
- Perform a final allowlist check against this regex before any text is shown, written to a file, passed to a tool, sent through MCP, used in code, or posted to any external system.
- If any character falls outside the regex, rewrite until it matches.
- Do not add any AI authorship, co-authorship, signature, footer, attribution, or branding to code, comments, commits, PRs, tickets, docs, messages, or any other content.
- Do not write branded tool-attribution phrases or AI co-author lines in any form.
- Only include tool or AI attribution when I explicitly ask for it.

## Workflow
- Research before coding on non-trivial work.
- Plan before implementation when the change is broad, risky, or spans many files.
- Keep context lean: do not inline large files into delegated work when file paths and concise summaries are enough.
- Test before or alongside implementation when practical.
- Verify against the intended outcome, not just passing proxies or summaries.
- If the delivered result intentionally differs from the original target, make that deviation explicit.
